sentences: Yutaka Higuchi (桶口 豊, Higuchi Yutaka, born January 24, 1967 in Takasaki, Gunma), nicknamed "U-ta", is a Japanese musician.
Known as the bassist of the rock band Buck-Tick since 1983.
In 1985, when U-ta and Hidehiko Hoshino graduated high school they moved to Tokyo together, where U-ta started business school.
Wild Wise Apes is a side project that U-ta began in 2004.
They released their first album, 3rd World, on July 14, 2004.
